Content:
Best centering (vert. and hor.) solution ever:
.outer { position: relative; }
.inner {
  position: absolute;
  top: 50%; left: 50%;
  transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
}<p><div class=&quot;outer&quot;>
  <div class=&quot;inner&quot;></div>
</div><p>This way you don&#x27;t need to know the width or height of inner element...
